description: The first ever American-Japanese creatively co-produced comic book! Set in the future, this series concerns the planet Earth after it has been ridden with death, disease and decay before being abandoned for cities in outer space. When a group with various psychic abilities returns to Earth in the hope that it has recovered, they are shocked by what awaits them.

The Psychonauts return from space to save Earth to find that it is populated with dinosaurs...and they're not friendly! Will the mutant adventurers give up on their dream of making Earth inhabitable again?

The action escalates in the penultimate issue of this riveting series! Still on Earth trying to determine whether the trashed planet can ever be populated again, the Psychonauts fall prey to a demon who is determined to see their mission fail. And if it means their deaths, so be it!

The ground-breaking series concludes. The Psychonauts confront the shadowy menace that has followed them since their arrival on Earth, while determining whether life on the devastated planet is feasible again.
Showing off all of the weapons at Frank Castle's disposal.

Introducing the Beeg-Time Crime Lords, featuring the first appearance of Tank & Brenner: Mall Cops and a special guest-appearance by Powdered Toast Man!! All of this plus “Ren Hoek for President" and “Commander Hoek & Cadet Stimpy: Alien Attack”
